BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NieR: Orchestra Concert 12026 [YoRHa]!
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261107T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261107T214500
DTSTAMP:20260707T014648Z
UID:occ-497@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:1
CATEGORIES:Instrumental Concert
DESCRIPTION:Music from Square Enix's NieR games — full orchestra\, choru
 s\, original vocalists\, and a new narrated Automata prequel story.\n\nThe
  music of the NieR video games performed live\, presented by AWR Music Pro
 ductions and Square Enix. Eric Roth conducts a full orchestra and chorus\,
  joined by J'Nique Nicole and Emi Evans\, the singers whose voices defined
  the original game recordings. Between the music\, recorded narration from
  NieR:Automata's Japanese voice cast — including Yui Ishikawa as 2B — 
 tells the story of the Pearl Harbor Descent Operation\, the prequel to Aut
 omata\, with visuals on a giant screen. A follow-up from the team behind t
 he earlier NieR:Orchestra Concert [the end of data] tour.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260701T035939Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CANCELLED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetEventList?groupC
 ode=NIE&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Death Becomes Her
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261117T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261117T220000
DTSTAMP:20260707T014648Z
UID:occ-1356@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The Broadway musical of the 1992 camp classic: two frenemies\,
  one youth potion\, and a grudge built to outlast death.\n\nThe musical ad
 apted from the 1992 Robert Zemeckis film: fading actress Madeline Ashton a
 nd long-suffering writer Helen Sharp have spent decades as frenemies\, and
  the feud turns supernatural when a mysterious potion restores their youth
  and makes the grudge eternal. Book by Marco Pennette\, with songs by Juli
 a Mattison and Noel Carey. Tony winner Christopher Gattelli directs and ch
 oreographs. Variety called it "a laugh-filled\, tuneful musical to die for
 ."
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260707T013014Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetGroupList?groupC
 ode=DBH&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
